;; Pair2 fixture build (rf2-cxik; rf2-kp1d8 flipped to `:deps true`).
;;
;; A minimal shadow-cljs build that mounts the counter view and preloads
;; `re-frame-pair2.runtime`. Used by pair2's tests/shim, tests/e2e, and
;; tests/prompts surfaces, plus tools/mcp-conformance's hermetic
;; orchestrator (`run-live-pair2-overflow-hermetic.cjs`).
;;
;; The two pair2-specific bits are:
;;
;;   1. The `../../preload` source path — directory carrying the
;;      `re_frame_pair2/runtime.cljs` namespace that ships in the
;;      `@day8/re-frame-pair2` npm package's `preload/`. Pair2's SKILL.md
;;      §Setup tells consumers to put `node_modules/@day8/re-frame-pair2/preload`
;;      on the build's source paths; here we point straight at the
;;      in-repo source. With `:deps true` the source-paths live in
;;      `deps.edn` `:paths`, not here.
;;
;;   2. `:devtools :preloads [re-frame-pair2.runtime]` — shadow-cljs's
;;      standard mechanism for loading the namespace before app code,
;;      so the load-time sentinel (`js/globalThis.__re_frame_pair2_runtime`)
;;      is in place by the time `discover-app` probes.
;;
;; `:deps true` (rf2-kp1d8) routes classpath resolution through this
;; artefact's `deps.edn`. The earlier shape declared `:dependencies`
;; here AND a parallel set of `:local/root` entries in `deps.edn` —
;; shadow-cljs's own `:dependencies` slot wins when both are present,
;; so the `:local/root "../../../../implementation/core"` entry (and
;; therefore `re-frame.core`) was silently dropped and the build
;; failed with "namespace re-frame.core not available". Same idiom
;; as `tools/pair2-mcp/shadow-cljs.edn` (rf2-obpa9).
;;
;; The nREPL port file lands at `.shadow-cljs/nrepl.port` (shadow-cljs
;; 3.x default cache-root); the hermetic orchestrator and pair2-mcp's
;; `read-port-from-fs` both probe that path plus the legacy
;; `target/shadow-cljs/nrepl.port` and `.nrepl-port` fallbacks.
{:deps     true
 :nrepl    {:port 0}  ;; let shadow choose; pair2 reads the port file.
 :dev-http {8030 "public"}
 :builds
 {:app
  {:target     :browser
   :output-dir "public/out"
   :asset-path "/out"
   :modules    {:main {:init-fn counter.core/run}}
   :devtools   {:preloads [re-frame-pair2.runtime]}}}}
